- otherwise use forecast = `SUM(Actuals E:G) / (12 - D3)`

So the right combined formula pattern for each cell in `H6:P9` is:

`=IF(SUMIFS(...)<>0, SUMIFS(...), SUM($Erow:$Grow)/(12-$D$3))`

This preserves the existing month-specific `SUMIFS` logic while falling back to the forecast amount when there is no actual for that period.

